gomodel:SYNGO_191  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Voltage clamp experiments in the Calyx of Held using the specific blocker for Kv1.2 TsTX-Kalpha. Note that in this study the Kv1.2 channels are presynaptically very close to but not in the Calyx terminal.. Experimental description: MM: p.28: Cochlear nucleus and brainstem slices (100-150 mm thick) were prepared as previously described (Rusznak et al. 1997; Dodson et al. 2002). 8-14 day old Wistar and Lister Hooded rats were killed by decapitation in accordance with the UK Animals -- Highlighted 15 Feb 2017" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_191" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

